                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">713.1311/121: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Costa Rica (<persName type="to">Eberhardt</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 11, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>37. Your despatch No. 1168, October 28.<note n="1" xml:id="d346fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> Associated Press despatch published in <hi rend="italic">La
                        Prensa</hi>, New York, dated San José, November 9, states that President
                        <persName corresp="#p_JOR1">Jiménez</persName> has announced that he will
                    denounce the Treaty of Peace and Amity of 1923.<note n="2" xml:id="d346fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Conference on Central American Affairs</hi>, p.
                        287.</note> Please report by telegraph. Department does not desire you to
                    discuss this matter with Costa Rican officials beyond a possible inquiry for
                    confirmation of this report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
